cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.CL 

The paper focuses on learning binary hash codes for similarity search tasks in computer vision and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new loss function and training scheme, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also evaluates its approach on information retrieval tasks, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper uses multi-indexing, which is a technique commonly used in multimedia retrieval (cs.MM). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of natural language processing techniques for evaluating the performance of their approach, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL).
